title: Have you seen this 1950s Chevrolet?
text:
Credit: Sussex Police Police are searching for a valuable and distinctive American 1950's car, stolen from a speed festival in West Sussex.
During the afternoon of Sunday 13 September the 1956 red and white Chevrolet Bel Air Coupe, registration number TAS 501, valued at Â£70,000, was stolen from a public area at the Goodwood Festival of Speed.
Last updated Wed 30 Sep 2015 Travel
